nWeismann, who quit the presidency of\nthe World Zionist Organization two\nweeks ago, was made by Judge Julian\ni W Mack, honorary chairman of the\n1 Zionist Organization of America, be\nfore he sailed for home yesterday.\nJudge Mack declared Dr. Weismann.\nwho resigned as a protest against the\nBritish white paper, was not responsi\nble so- the present Zionist situation.\nThe blame was on the entire Jewish\npeople, he said, who were unable to\nbuild up Palestine at a more rapid\npace.\nThe American Zionist leader warned\nthat if Dr. Welzmann's resignation was\naccepted by the Actions Committee it\nwould result in the loss of Zionist\nfriends in the ranks of the Conserva\ni tlve. Liberal and Labor parties.\n\u25a0hi.i in i mi i in i ii\u2014\u2014\u2014W\nMERCANTILE MARINE\nOFFICIAL TO RETIRE\nft\nJohn H. Thomas, Who Got Start\nin Baltimore, Troubled With\nPoor Health.\n\nNEW YORK. November 7.\u2014The re\ntirement of John H. Thomas, vice presi\ndent of the International Mercantile\nMarine Co., to tak\u00a3 effect next Decem\nber 31. was announced yesterday by\n11\np a. a mekbni |fiaMet* H \u00bbe\nTO sHftfni*Jwis bwl (fit Maryland,\nand began *ml 'ahipplrtk career with\nPumess \\v thy fe Co .in Baltimore Hf\ncame MJMw York in ISM. fin recent\nrears; MJ has been active In the opera\ntion,** the Panama Pacific line, a\nsufindhtry of the International Mer\ncantile Marine. Poor health was given\nas the cause of his retirement.\nBven Columbus as he set out on hu\njourney acmes tbe Atlantic had wanted\nto reach the magic land of gold\u2014the\nIndies\u2014and when he landed in Haiti\nhe believed he was in the place \u201cwhere\nthe earth waa hiding her greatest\nriches.","height":"25290","width":"19725"}}
